MOH: 3 new confirmed MERS-CoV cases recorded in the Kingdom's regions
---------------------------------------------------------------------
Daily situation report on cases of MERS-CoV infection [28 May 2014]

Total number of confirmed cases in the last 24 hours: 3 cases.
Recovered and discharged cases that previously tested positive and are now negative: 4 cases.
Total number of deaths: 6 (2 cases were recorded over the past 24 hours and the other 4 are previously confirmed cases).

Overview of the health status of the cases:
- 1 stable case
- 2 deaths

Details of the health situation of the cases:
Riyadh
------
- a 72-year-old male suffering from diabetes and hypertension. He developed respiratory symptoms on [5 May 2014] and was admitted to a government hospital on [26 May 2014]. His condition is stable and is isolated at home.

Makkah
------
- a 65-year-old suffering from diabetes, hypertension, heart disease, and chronic obstructive pulmonary disease. He was admitted to a government hospital on [26 May 2014]. He has been in contact with a confirmed case. He passed away on [27 May 2014].
- a 39-year-old female suffering from diabetes, hypertension, systemic lupus erythematosus, and is a steroid user. She developed fever, mild cough, and joint pain. She was admitted to a government hospital on [21 May 2014]. She has been in contact with a confirmed case. She passed away on [27 May 2014].

Deaths of previously reported cases:
- a 36-year-old male was admitted to a government hospital in Madinah. He was previously recorded as a confirmed case on [12 May 2014]. He passed away on [27 May 2014].
- a 51-year-old male was admitted to a government hospital in Madinah. He was previously recorded as a confirmed case on [19 May 2014]. He passed away on [27 May 2014].
- a 55-year-old female was admitted to a government hospital in Riyadh. She was previously recorded as a confirmed case on [14 May 2014]. She passed away on [27 May 2014].
- an 80-year-old female was admitted to a government hospital in Riyadh. She was previously recorded as a confirmed case on [28 May 2014].

Recovery of previously reported cases:
- a 36-year-old female was discharged from a government hospital in Riyadh on [27 May 2014].
- a 40-year-old female was discharged from a government hospital in Riyadh on [27 May 2014].
- a 40-year-old female was discharged from a government hospital in Riyadh on [27 May 2014].
- a 48-year-old female was discharged from a government hospital in Taif on [27 May 2014].

