[2] Jordan, 1 new case confirmation: WHO 28 May 2014
Date: Wed 28 May 2014
Source: WHO Global Alert and Response (GAR), Disease Outbreak News [edited]
http://www.who.int/csr/don/2014_05_28_mers/en/


Middle East respiratory syndrome coronavirus (MERS-CoV) -- update 28 May 2014
----------------------------------------------------------------------
On 25 May 2014, the National IHR [International Health Regulations] Focal Point of Jordan reported to WHO an additional Middle East respiratory syndrome coronavirus (MERS-CoV) case in Amman, Jordan.

The case is a 69-year-old male Jordanian citizen and resident of Amman governorate. The patient was admitted to hospital on [29 Apr 2014] for a surgical procedure. He was discharged on 3 May 2014. On [8 May 2014], the patient presented with fever. His condition deteriorated and he was admitted to the same hospital on [11 May 2014]. 2 days later, on [13 May 2014], he started to complain of cough. A specimen collected from the patient tested negative for MERS on the same day, but a chest X-ray showed pneumonia. A 2nd specimen was collected and it tested positive by PCR on [23 May 2014]. The patient is currently in the intensive care unit in critical condition.

The patient is known to have comorbidities, no history of travel, and no history of contact with animals. He also has no history of contact with a laboratory confirmed MERS-CoV case. However, he was admitted to the same hospital where a laboratory confirmed MERS-CoV fatal case was admitted. This case was reported to WHO on [6 May 2014].

Contact tracing and screening of family members, health workers, and patients for MERS-CoV is currently ongoing.

Globally, 636 laboratory-confirmed cases of infection with MERS-CoV have officially been reported to WHO, including 193 deaths. This global total includes all of the cases reported in this update, plus 17 laboratory confirmed cases officially reported to WHO by Saudi Arabia between [16 and 18 May 2014]. WHO is working closely with Saudi Arabia for additional information on these cases and will provide further updates as soon as possible.

--
